HINT: If you aren't sure which aspects are taxable, then consult your local state board of equalization or an accountant.<br> 
In most cases you will be responsible for sales tax on any fee which you charge to the customer that is either beyond your cost for the service
(e.g. if you profit from shipping then it is taxable in most states) OR if it is an actual service you provide e.g. Gift Wrapping. 
These rules vary SUBSTANTIALLY from state to state - there is no uniform sales tax code, consult your state board of equalization or an
accountant who is familiar with sales tax (not necessarily a CPA who specializes in personal income tax). 
